Derivatives of GELU

Source: R/gelu.R
dGELU.Rd

Derivatives of GELU

Usage

dGELU(x)

d2GELU(x)

d3GELU(x)

d4GELU(x)

Arguments

x

numeric vector

Value

numeric vector

See also

Other Activation Functions: ELU(), GELU(), PReLU(), ReLU(), SELU(), Swish(), dELU(), dPReLU(), dReLU(), dSELU(), dSwish(), dlReLU(), dsoftplus(), lReLU(), softplus()

Examples

dGELU(c(-2, -1, 0, 1, 2))
#> [1] -0.08523180 -0.08331547  0.50000000  1.08331547  1.08523180
d2GELU(c(-2, -1, 0, 1, 2))
#> [1] -0.1079819  0.2419707  0.7978846  0.2419707 -0.1079819
d3GELU(c(-2, -1, 0, 1, 2))
#> [1]  0.0000000  0.7259122  0.0000000 -0.7259122  0.0000000
d4GELU(c(-2, -1, 0, 1, 2))
#> [1]  0.4319277  0.4839414 -1.5957691  0.4839414  0.4319277
# you can use rxode2 as well
r <- rxode2({
   r1 <- dGELU(time)
   r2 <- d2GELU(time)
   r3 <- d3GELU(time)
   r4 <- d4GELU(time)
})
